    <text>
        <body>
            <div>

	<gb type="book-page-margins"/>

	<!-- Megan, the various EIC comments below refer to the page numbers of the undertext. AW -->

	<pb facs="liv_000200_0001" n="0001"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_001r_0_C_color" n="001r"/>--><!-- Process blots on this page. AW -->       
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">for the isolation in which they live
<lb/>The head of <persName ref="people.xml#pers0107">Moenekuss</persName> is said to be
<lb/>preserved in a pot in his house
<lb/>and all public <add place="above"><metamark/></add> matters are gravely

	
	<pb facs="liv_000200_0002" n="0002"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_001v_0_C_color" n="001v"/>--><!-- Process blots on this page. AW -->
<lb/>communicated to it as if his spirit
<lb/>dwelt therein - His body was eaten
<lb/>The flesh removed from the head
<lb/>and eaten too - His <choice><sic>fathers</sic><corr>father's</corr></choice> head is
<lb/>said to <unclear cert="high">be kept</unclear> also</p>

    
	<pb facs="liv_000200_0003" n="0003"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_002r_0_C_color" n="002r"/>-->
<lb/><p>The foregoing refers to <placeName><settlement type="village" ref="settlement.xml#sett0002">Bambarre</settlement></placeName>
<lb/>alone - In other districts graves <choice><orig>shew</orig><reg>show</reg></choice>
<lb/>that <choice><orig>sepulture</orig><reg>sepulcher</reg></choice> is customary - Here no
<lb/>grave appears - Some admit the

    
	<pb facs="liv_000200_0004" n="0004"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_002v_0_C_color" n="002v"/>-->
<lb/>existence of the practice here - others
<lb/>deny it - In the <placeName><region ref="region.xml#region0007"><foreign xml:lang="und"><term xml:lang="und" ref="foreign-word.xml#frgn0009"><placeName><region ref="region.xml#region0007"><geogName type="forest" ref="geogName.xml#geog0041">Metamba</geogName></region></placeName></term></foreign> country</region></placeName>
<lb/>and <w>adjac<subst><del><gap extent="3" unit="chars"/></del><add place="over-text">ent</add></subst></w> to<!-- Megan, take a look at how I've done the <del><add> in this line. AW --> <placeName><geogName type="river" ref="geogName.xml#geog0033">Lualaba</geogName></placeName> - a quarrel with
<lb/>a wife often ends in the husband killing
<lb/>her and eating her heart mixed up

    
	<pb facs="liv_000200_0005" n="0005"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_003r_0_C_color" n="003r"/>-->
<lb/>in a huge mess of <choice><sic><term type="animal">goat</term>s</sic><corr><term type="animal">goat</term>'s</corr></choice> flesh -
<lb/>This has the charm character - fingers
<lb/>are taken as charms in other parts 
<lb/>In <placeName><settlement type="village" ref="settlement.xml#sett0002">Bambarre</settlement></placeName> alone is the depraved

    
	<pb facs="liv_000200_0006" n="0006"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_003v_0_C_color" n="003v"/>--><!-- Process bits at page bottom? AW -->
<lb/>taste the motive for cannibalism</p><!-- I removed <space> for the empty space on this page. Not needed. Only do this for vertial space when it intervenes between lines and be sure to add dim="vertical" in those cases. AW -->

    
	<pb facs="liv_000200_0007" n="0007"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_004r_0_C_color" n="004r"/>--><!-- EIC 474 -->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><unclear cert="medium">On</unclear><!-- Check processed images for this. AW --> <date when="1870-08-17">17<hi rend="sup">th</hi> August 1870</date> <persName ref="people.xml#pers0118">Monamyembo</persName>
<lb/>the <term type="occupation">chief</term> who was punished by <persName ref="people.xml#pers0002"><choice><abbr>M</abbr><expan>Muhamad</expan></choice> Bogharib</persName>
<lb/>lately came <add place="above"><metamark/></add> bring two <term type="animal">goats</term> - One
<lb/>he gave to <persName ref="people.xml#pers0002">Muhamad</persName> the other to
<lb/><persName ref="people.xml#pers0107"><choice><orig>Moenekus</orig><reg>Moenekuss</reg></choice></persName>' son acknowledging
<lb/>that he had killed his elder brother
    
	<pb facs="liv_000200_0008" n="0008"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_004v_0_C_color" n="004v"/>--><!-- EIC 473 -->
<lb/>He had killed eleven persons over
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="words"/><add place="inspace" rend="small">in our <space extent="3" unit="words"/>absence</add>
<lb/>at <placeName><geogName type="river" ref="geogName.xml#geog0040">Luamo</geogName></placeName> - in addition to those
<!--<lb/>at <placeName><geogName type="river" ref="geogName.xml#geog0040">Luamo</geogName></placeName> <add place="above">in our <space extent="3" unit="words"/>absence</add> - in addition to those--><!-- Line recoded to improve transformation. AW -->
<lb/>killed in villages on our <choice><abbr>SE</abbr><expan>South East</expan></choice> when
<lb/>we were away - It transpired
<lb/>that <persName ref="people.xml#pers0062"><w><subst><del>T</del><add place="over-text">K</add></subst>andahara</w></persName> brother of old
<lb/><persName ref="people.xml#pers0107">Moenekuss</persName> whose village is

	<pb facs="liv_000200_0009" n="0009"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_005r_0_C_color" n="005r"/>-->   
<lb/>near this - killed 3 women &amp; a child and
<lb/>that a <add place="below">^</add> <orgName><add place="above"><term type="occupation">trading</term></add> man</orgName> came over from <placeName><settlement type="village">Kasangangazi</settlement></placeName>
<lb/>and was murdered too for no reason but
<lb/>to eat his body - <persName ref="people.xml#pers0002">Muhamad</persName> ordered old
<lb/><persName ref="people.xml#pers0062"><choice><orig><w>Tanda<add place="over-text">h</add>ara</w></orig><reg>Kandahara</reg></choice></persName><!-- This is transcribed as "Kandahara" in the Last Journals, but it looks like an "L" to me. MW. --><!-- See how I've corrected it. AW --> to <subst><del><gap extent="1" unit="words" agent="overwriting"/></del><add place="over-text">bring</add></subst> ten goats and take <!-- The addition in this line looks like a different color. Worth processing? AW -->
		
	<pb facs="liv_000200_0010" n="0010"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_005v_0_C_color" n="005v"/>--><!-- Process blots on this page. AW -->   
<lb/>them over to <placeName><settlement type="village">Kasangangazi</settlement></placeName> to pay
<lb/>for the murdered <subst><del><gap extent="1" unit="words" agent="overwriting"/></del><add place="over-text">man</add></subst> - When they <!-- The addition in this line looks like a different color. Worth processing? AW -->
<lb/>tell of each other's deeds they disclose
<lb/>a horrid state of bloodthirsty callousness
	
	<pb facs="liv_000200_0011" n="0011"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_006r_0_C_color" n="006r"/>-->
<lb/>People over hill <choice><abbr>NNE</abbr><expan>North North East</expan></choice> of this killed a
<lb/>person out hoeing - if a cultivator is alone
<lb/>he is almost sure of being slain.</p>
<lb/><p>Some said that people in the vicinity
<lb/>or <term type="animal"><choice><orig>hyaenas</orig><reg>hyenas</reg></choice></term> stole the buried dead, but
<lb/><persName ref="people.xml#pers0145">Posho</persName>'s wife died and in <term type="tribe" ref="ethnic-group.xml#ethnic0014"><choice><orig>Wanyamesi</orig><reg>Nyamwezi</reg></choice></term>
    
	<pb facs="liv_000200_0012" n="0012"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_006v_0_C_color" n="006v"/>-->
<lb/>fashion was thrown out of camp <w>un<supplied>-</supplied>
<lb break="no"/>buried</w> - <persName ref="people.xml#pers0002">Muhamad</persName> threatened an attack if
<lb/><term type="tribe" ref="ethnic-group.xml#ethnic0010">Manyema</term> did not cease exhuming the 
<lb/>dead - it was effectual - neither men nor
<lb/><term type="animal"><choice><orig>hyaenas</orig><reg>hyenas</reg></choice></term> touched her though exposed now
<lb/>for <measure>seven days</measure> <date when="1870-08-24">24<hi rend="sup">th</hi> August 1870</date></p><!-- Though it seems right, I'm not sure we should put a <p> before the date here. AW -->
    
	<pb facs="liv_000200_0013" n="0013"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_007r_0_C_color" n="007r"/>--><!-- EIC foootnote -->
<lb/><p><space extent="1" unit="words"/>When the <seg type="weather">rains ceased</seg> in <date when="1870-06">June</date><!-- Megan, note the corrections I've made to this line. AW -->
<lb/>I wished to go Northwards along the 
<lb/><placeName><geogName type="river" ref="geogName.xml#geog0033">Lualaba</geogName></placeName> &amp; buy a canoe but my
<lb/><term type="occupation">attendants</term> professed fear of the water</p>
<lb/><p>I then promised not to buy a canoe
<lb/><lb/>
    
	<pb facs="liv_000200_0014" n="0014"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_007v_0_C_color" n="007v"/>--><!-- EIC footnote -->
<lb/>but this elicited that they were determined
<lb/>not to go at all - the head <orgName>Arabs</orgName> told
<lb/>me that they were in the habit of going
<lb/>to the women whose husbands were
<lb/>away and getting food and spending
<lb/>the night with them <space extent="1" unit="words"/>- They then
    
	<pb facs="liv_000200_0015" n="0015"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_008r_0_C_color" n="008r"/>--><!-- EIC footnote -->
<lb/>refused rations - not understanding 
<lb/>why I <choice><orig>enquired</orig><reg>inquiried</reg></choice> the reason = they replied <!-- Megan, note changes in this line. Also note that DL often runs "I" onto other words, so just separate silently. AW -->
<lb/>that the beads were not enough - the
<lb/><orgName>Arabs</orgName> said "they are about to desert<unclear cert="medium">"</unclear> &amp;
<lb/><choice><sic>'</sic><corr>"</corr></choice>that is a <orgName>slave</orgName> custom<supplied cert="medium">"</supplied> -</p>
	
	<pb facs="liv_000200_0016" n="0016"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_008v_0_C_color" n="008v"/>--><!-- EIC footnote -->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">I <w>spo<subst><del><gap extent="2" unit="chars" agent="overwriting"/></del><add>k</add></subst>e</w> long to them advising them
<lb/>earnestly not to desert &amp; lose all their
<lb/>arrears of pay - - But on going out
<lb/>from me one called out <space extent="1" unit="words"/>"Who
<lb/>will he get to carry his
    
	<pb facs="liv_000200_0017" n="0017"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_009r_0_C_color" n="009r"/>-->
<lb/>things" - then a loud <supplied>"</supplied>Ha ha ha<supplied>"</supplied> to make
<lb/>me hear it. On telling them that <persName ref="people.xml#pers0158">Seyed
<lb/>Majid</persName> had punished those who deserted
<lb/><persName ref="people.xml#pers0170">Speke</persName> &amp; the <term type="occupation">consul</term> would certainly be
<lb/>angry to hear that I had been thrown
<lb/>away by them in the middle of the cannibal
    
	<pb facs="liv_000200_0018" n="0018"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_009v_0_C_color" n="009v"/>--><!-- EIC footnote -->
<lb/>country where I could get no <term type="occupation">carriers</term>
<lb/>as the <term type="tribe" ref="ethnic-group.xml#ethnic0010">Manyema</term> will not go to the next
<lb/>village - <persName ref="people.xml#pers0168">Simon</persName> said "give me a bit
<lb/>of paper to tell that I am a very bad
<lb/>boy" - This was supposed to be witty
<lb/>&amp; he added <supplied>"</supplied>let <persName ref="people.xml#pers0158">Seyed Majid</persName> chain

	<pb facs="liv_000200_0019" n="0019"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_0010r_0_C_color" n="0010r"/>-->
<lb/>me - beat me - shoot me<choice><sic>'</sic><corr>"</corr></choice> I <choice><sic>want</sic><corr>wanted</corr></choice> to go to <placeName><geogName type="river" ref="geogName.xml#geog0033">Lualaba</geogName></placeName>
<lb/><persName ref="people.xml#pers0008">Abram</persName> said the others intended to throw down my
<lb/>bundles &amp; run away in the forest - "He was <unclear cert="medium">tired</unclear>
<lb/>with seven <choice><sic>years</sic><corr>years'</corr></choice> work" These two are the <unclear cert="medium">bring</unclear> <gap extent="1" unit="words" agent="fading"/><!-- Spectral processing may help here or Agnes's transciption. Same for next line. AW -->
<lb/><persName ref="people.xml#pers0065">Katomba</persName> at whose voice they trembled <unclear cert="medium">spel<gap extent="2" unit="words" agent="fading"/></unclear>
    
	<pb facs="liv_000200_0020" n="0020"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_0010v_0_C_color" n="0010v"/>--><!-- Spectral processing on left-hand side of the page. AW -->
<lb/>in <unclear cert="medium"><w><gap extent="2" unit="chars" agent="fading"/>ly</w></unclear> &amp; they said they would go but seeing
<lb/><unclear cert="medium"><w><gap extent="3" unit="chars" agent="fading"/><supplied cert="medium">tha</supplied>t</w></unclear> he did nothing again refused - The knowledge
<lb/><unclear cert="medium">that</unclear> I <choice><sic>wont</sic><corr>won't</corr></choice> punish as the <orgName>Arabs</orgName> do is the
<lb/><w><gap extent="1" unit="chars" agent="fading"/><supplied cert="medium">r</supplied>eason</w> on their desertion - the murders
<lb/><unclear cert="medium">they</unclear> committed at <placeName><settlement type="village">Kabuire</settlement></placeName> <w>dest<gap extent="2" unit="chars" agent="blot"/><supplied>ro</supplied>yed</w> what
    
	<pb facs="liv_000200_0021" n="0021"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_0011r_0_C_color" n="0011r"/>-->
<lb/>little of moral nature they possessed - I would
<lb/>not have brought them from <placeName><settlement type="village" ref="settlement.xml#sett0014">Ujiji</settlement></placeName> as the <unclear cert="medium">deterioration</unclear>
<lb/>was then visible in stealing from me to pay their
<lb/>prostitutes but <persName ref="people.xml#pers0183">Thani</persName> behaved so strangely to
<lb/><bibl>my packet of letters</bibl>, refusing it - than send

	<pb facs="liv_000200_0022" n="0022"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_0011v_0_C_color" n="0011v"/>-->
<lb/>it back "because he did not know the contents"
<lb/>I feared its destruction and then I should be
<lb/>waiting for other men from <placeName><geogName type="island" ref="geogName.xml#geog0060">Zanzibar</geogName></placeName> in vain
<lb/>I therefore strained my utmost to finish up
<lb/><choice><sic>up</sic><corr/></choice> my work with what I had

    <pb facs="liv_000200_0023" n="0023"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_0012r_0_C_color" n="0012r"/>--><!-- EIC right margin -->
<lb/>But now these worthless <orgName>slaves</orgName> had me
<lb/>at their mercy &amp; wished to be masters - to take
<lb/>what beads they chose and go or remain just
<lb/>as it suited their fancy - they thought that

	<pb facs="liv_000200_0024" n="0024"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_0012v_0_C_color" n="0012v"/>--><!-- EIC left margin -->
<lb/>I did not know where they got food and when
<lb/>declaring their rations of beads too small they
<lb/>bought grass cloth clothing, knives spears
<lb/>and <term type="foodstuff">dainties</term> - With three <persName ref="people.xml#pers0179">Susi</persName> - <persName ref="people.xml#pers0029">Chuma</persName> <!-- Adrian, if dainties are candies should they be tagged as foodstuff? HB --><!-- Done. AW -->

    <pb facs="liv_000200_0025" n="0025"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_0013r_0_C_color" n="0013r"/>-->
<lb/>and <persName ref="people.xml#pers0039">Gardner</persName> I set off - intending to join <persName ref="people.xml#pers0002"><choice><abbr>M-</abbr><expan>Muhamad</expan></choice>
<lb/>Bogharib</persName> or <persName ref="people.xml#pers0058">Josuf</persName> on <placeName><geogName type="river" ref="geogName.xml#geog0033">Lualaba</geogName></placeName> -  We went
<lb/>with three <term type="occupation">deputies</term> from the head <orgName>Arabs</orgName> &amp;
<lb/>their <orgName>slaves</orgName> - but they hated me &amp; tried to get

<!-- AW transcription begins -->
			
    <pb facs="liv_000200_0026" n="0026"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_0013v_0_C_color" n="0013v"/>--><!-- EIC left margin -->
<lb/>away from me - I however kept up and
<lb/>on the fourth day passed through nine villages
<lb/>destroyed by the worthies who did not wish
<lb/>me to see more of their work - Then

    <pb facs="liv_000200_0027" n="0027"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_0014r_0_C_color" n="0014r"/>--><!-- EIC right margin -->
<lb/>met with <persName ref="people.xml#pers0002"><choice><orig>Mohamad</orig><reg>Muhamad</reg></choice> Bogharib</persName> &amp; <persName ref="people.xml#pers0058"><choice><orig>Josuph</orig><reg>Josuf</reg></choice></persName> coming
<lb/>back from <placeName><settlement type="village" ref="settlement.xml#sett0005"><persName ref="people.xml#pers0064">Kasongo</persName>'s</settlement></placeName> - I slept at a village
<lb/>a little way from them &amp; was met in morning
<lb/>with the news that a man of the party which

    <pb facs="liv_000200_0028" n="0028"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_0014v_0_C_color" n="0014v"/>--><!-- EIC left margin -->
<lb/>eschewed <app><rdg>any</rdg><rdg>my</rdg></app> company had been stabbed by
<lb/>night in revenge for the slaughter of relatives
<lb/>&amp; burning of nine villages - <persName ref="people.xml#pers0002"><choice><orig>Mohamad</orig><reg>Muhamad</reg></choice></persName>
<lb/>refused to engage in a wholesale manner

    <pb facs="liv_000200_0029" n="0029"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_0015r_0_C_color" n="0015r"/>--><!-- EIC right margin -->
<lb/>to revenge the dead one and seeing that I had no
<lb/>friend &amp; only three people I turned back - the
<lb/>mud was grievous &amp; as I waded it all
<lb/>my feet were torn to pieces and <term type="ailment" ref="ailment.xml#ailm0015">irritable

    <pb facs="liv_000200_0030" n="0030"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_0015v_0_C_color" n="0015v"/>--><!-- EIC left margin -->
<lb/>eating ulcers</term> begun which have <w>dis-
<lb break="no"/>abled</w> me ever since - I now spoke with my
<lb/>friend <persName ref="people.xml#pers0002">Muhamad</persName> and he offered to go with <!-- DL spells it both Mohamad and Muhamad. I've arbitrarily decided to treat the latter as the "normal" version. AW -->
<lb/>me to see <placeName><geogName type="river" ref="geogName.xml#geog0033">Lualaba</geogName></placeName> from <placeName><geogName type="river" ref="geogName.xml#geog0040">Luamo</geogName></placeName> - but

    <pb facs="liv_000200_0031" n="0031"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_0016r_0_C_color" n="0016r"/>--><!-- EIC right margin -->
<lb/>I explained that merely to see &amp; measure
<lb/>its depth would not do - I must see whither
<lb/>it went - This would require a number of his
<lb/>people in lieu of my deserters &amp; <add place="inspace">to</add> take

    <pb facs="liv_000200_0032" n="0032"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297a_0016v_0_C_color" n="0016v"/>-->
<lb/>them away from his ivory trade which
<lb/>at present is like gold digging - <subst><del>To</del><add place="over-text">^</add> <add place="above">I must</add></subst> make
<lb/>amends &amp; I offered him two thousands
<lb/>Rupees &amp; a gun worth seven hundred

    <pb facs="liv_000200_0033" n="0033"/>
